com.atlassian.jira.issue.index.DefaultIndexManager#reIndexIssues calls for await function which return type is void, so it dosn't know was reindexing complete sucessful or not. It just wait for random time to return control flow up to stack, but all indexing job does in background thread.

Simply this shouldn't be calling for await/obtain to improve response timings.

